# If and switch

**`if`/`elseif`/`else`** for general branching. **`switch`** can simplify multiple string cases and supports **`-Regex`** / **`-Wildcard`**.

@section: switch default

Use **`default`** for the fallback case.

@section: Next step

Pair with **`try/catch`** for terminating errors (next lesson).

@quiz: What keyword defines the fallback branch in `switch`?
@option: else
@correct: default
@option: catch

@quiz: Are `-eq` string comparisons case-insensitive by default?
@option: Yes, always case-sensitive
@correct: No—use `-ceq` for case sensitivity
@option: Only on Linux
